main event: An oval-shaped unidentified flying object was observed over Champaign, Illinois, on September 22, 1960.
interesting points: The object was four times the size of the full moon., It wobbled as it traveled without emitting any sound or trail., The sighting lasted approximately 1 minute., The object changed direction during its fast flight., Observers noted that it may have reflected sunlight, appearing bright white.
witness description: young, impressionable boys who were positive about the object's characteristics
